InformasiMuatanScreen.infoBottomsheetCar:
• Raw Materials: Materials or components that have not been processed.
  • Semi-finished Goods: Products that have undergone several processing stages but are not yet complete.
  • Finished Goods: Final products ready for use or sale.
  • Others: Materials/goods that do not fit the above types but still have functions in production or distribution processes.

Selecting the right cargo type will help in management and shipping.

• Solid: Cargo in solid form.
  • Liquid: Cargo in liquid form, usually requires special handling.
  • Bulk: Cargo shipped in bulk, such as grains or sand.
  • Vehicle: Cargo in the form of transportation vehicles that need to be transported.
  • Container: Cargo packed in a container.

Selecting the right cargo category will help in management and shipping.
